		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.frivoli.com/caninenation/?p=483</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Training our dogs can be fun and frustrating, both for us and our dogs.  Humans and dogs have very different responses when progress goes slowly or in an unexpected direction.  How we, as humans, respond to those frustrating moments can have a large impact on our dogs ability or willingness to learn.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Audio edition of the article <a href="http://lifeasahuman.com/2011/pets/two-important-words-of-dog-training-advice/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><strong>Two Important Words of Dog Training Advice</strong></a> from the Life As A Human online magazine website. You can visit <a href="http://lifeasahuman.com/category/pets/canine-nation/" target="_blank">Life a a Human</a> to find this and other articles.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.frivoli.com/caninenation/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/two-words.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-506" title="What?" src="http://www.frivoli.com/caninenation/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/two-words.jpg" alt="What?" width="300" height="279" /></a>Training our dogs can be fun and frustrating, both for us and our dogs.  Humans and dogs have very different responses when progress goes slowly or in an unexpected direction.  How we, as humans, respond to those frustrating moments can have a large impact on our dogs ability or willingness to learn.  Sometimes the best thing we can do to help our dogs learn during training is to be quiet, be still, and give them time to work out what we&#8217;re asking for.</p>
<p>This week I&#8217;m asking you to <strong>SPREAD THE WORD</strong> about Canine Nation.  The Canine Nation written articles can be found at: <a href="http://www.lifeasahuman.com/categories/pets/canine-nation" target="_blank">http://www.lifeasahuman.com/categories/pets/canine-nation</a>  and the podcasts can be found here at: <a href="http://www.caninenation.ca" target="_blank">http://www.caninenation.ca</a>  And don&#8217;t forget, the Canine Nation podcasts are also available at <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">iTunes!</span></strong></p>
<p>If you know someone who would enjoy learning more about dogs, dog behaviour, or dog science, please let them know about Canine Nation.  It might be just the thing for those dog lovers in your life!</p>
