		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.frivoli.com/caninenation/?p=473</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[ Managing your dog when out in the world is just as important as training your dog to be a "good citizen."  Sometimes we can't anticipate all that the world can throw at our dogs and if they behave inappropriately, it could land you in serious trouble.  Your dog may even be taken away to be euthanised.  But there are lots of great ways you can protect your dog with a little common sense, the right equipment, and some vigilance.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Audio edition of the article <a href="http://lifeasahuman.com/2011/pets/defending-your-dog/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><strong>Defending Your Dog</strong></a> from the Life As A Human online magazine website. You can visit <a href="http://lifeasahuman.com/category/pets/canine-nation/" target="_blank">Life a a Human</a> to find this and other articles.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.frivoli.com/caninenation/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/defending.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-567" title="Defending" src="http://www.frivoli.com/caninenation/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/defending-199x300.jpg" alt="Defending" width="199" height="300" /></a>It wasn’t that long ago that the family dog was often a free-ranging rural or suburban dweller, happily spending his days exploring his fields or neighborhood. But as the times have changed, so has the role of the dog in our North American cultures.  Managing your dog when out in the world is just as important as training your dog to be a &#8220;good citizen.&#8221;  Sometimes we can&#8217;t anticipate all that the world can throw at our dogs and if they behave inappropriately, it could land you in serious trouble.  Your dog may even be taken away to be euthanised.  But there are lots of great ways you can protect your dog with a little common sense, the right equipment, and some vigilance.  We have to be prepared to defend our dog no matter what happens along the way.</p>
<p>Here is the <a href="http://lawvibe.com/dog-bite-law-top-7-ways-to-save-your-pet-from-euthanasia/" target="_blank">article I found on the Dog Bite Law website </a>on how to protect yourself and your dog from legal situations.</p>
<p>Information on dog legislation in <a href="http://www.dlcc.ca/" target="_blank">Canada</a>.<br />
Information on dogs and the law in the <a href="http://www.animallaw.info/topics/spcadangerousdogs.htm" target="_blank">US</a></p>
